<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--China-Fires     12-19 0150</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--China-Fires,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fires Kill and Injure 60,000 Chinese in Past Decade</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chinese have died in fires at a rate of seven per
day over the past decade, an official newspaper reported today.
   The China Daily said 410,000 fires killed or injured 60,000
people and caused $784 million in damage over the past 10 years.
   The report did not give a figure for deaths, but at seven
fatalities a day the total would be about 25,000.
   The daily, quoting the Ministry of Public Security's fire control
department, said the majority of fires are caused by human error,
negligence and failure to carry out fire safety measures.
   One-third of fires are a result of faulty electrical wiring in
buildings, it said, and senior officials of enterprises hit by fires
are rarely punished.
   The daily also quoted Beijing fire officials as saying their
communications and fire-fighting equipment are outdated.
</TEXT>
