<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Chile-Crash     12-19 0203</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Chile-Crash,0208</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Killed In Crash of Army Helicopter Seeking Deserter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An army helicopter searching for a
deserter crashed in the Andean foothills in southern Chile, killing
three officers, newspapers said today.
   Santiago newspapers cited unofficial sources as saying a colonel,
a major and a captain aboard the aircraft were killed when it
crashed on Sunday. A fourth occupant, an army mechanic, survived the
accident and was hospitalized in serious condition, the reports said.
   According to the reports, the helicopter, a French-made Lama, was
involved in a manhunt for a deserter from the army's 26th Regiment
based near the city of Coyhaique, about 1,300 miles south of
Santiago. The deserter reportedly was armed with an automatic rifle
and hand grenades
   Although no official army version of the crash was released, the
reports blamed the crash on heavy winds.
   Also on Sunday, an army lieutenant and two corporals were injured
in the bombing, apparently by leftist terrorists, of a highway
bridge on the country's main north-south highway 260 miles north of
Santiago.
   The officers were crossing the bridge in a car when the explosion
occurred, authorities said. The blast badly damaged the bridge, and
forced authorities to detour traffic.
</TEXT>
