<HEAD>Bomb Blasts Peace Corps Office In Honduras, No One Hurt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEGUCIGALPA, Honduras (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded early today outside
a U.S. Peace Corps building, damaging it and shattering nearby
windows, but no one was hurt, officials said.
   U.S. Embassy spokesman Charles Barclay described the bomb as
``powerful'' but said it caused little damage to the building.
