<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--HayWagonFatal     12-19 0183</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Hay Wagon Fatal,0186</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Boy Killed By Hay Wagon Filled With Christmas Carolers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SUMMERVILLE, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 6-year-old boy died after falling off
a hay wagon filled with Christmas carolers and being struck by a
wheel.
   ``Somehow he slipped getting onto the thing and fell back under
the wheel, and it went over him,'' said David Watson, the father of
the boy, Tommy Watson.
   ``I rubbed his face and told him I was Daddy, and I loved him and
told him to try to stay awake,'' said Watson, who has five other
children.
   The wagon, which held about 20 carolers, was pulled by a truck.
   The boy was pronounced dead on arrival Saturday night at a
hospital. The death was ruled accidental, said state Trooper W.D.
Cox.
   ``It was just one of those freak accidents that just happened,''
Watson said. ``The last minutes of his life were spent singing
Christmas carols and praising Jesus _ praising the Lord _ and he
spent the last few minutes of his life happy. He was a very happy
boy anyway. Now he's in heaven.''
</TEXT>
