<HEAD>Thousands Evacuated After World War II-Era Bomb Found</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Workers uncovered an unexploded
World War II bomb in a suburb Monday and evacuated all 5,000
residents, police said.
   Bomb disposal units planned to defuse the 1,000-pound device that
was found during excavation in the suburb of Sachsenhausen, a police
official said.
   About 90 patients were moved from a nearby hospital and trains
and traffic were rerouted, police said.
   Frankfurt was a major target of Allied bombing raids during the
war and the city was heavily damaged.
</TEXT>
