<HEAD>Two Killed in Downpour From Waterspout</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZAMBOANGA CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A waterspout off Sulu island
sent torrents of water cascading onto houses south of the provincial
capital of Jolo, killing at least two people, the military said
Monday.
   Nearly 100 families lost their homes in the storm Sunday night in
Jolo, about 600 miles south of Manila, according to police Lt. Col.
Eduardo Manaay.
