<HEAD>Robbery Suspects Killed by Resident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three men wearing ski masks and carrying guns were
killed early Monday after apparently trying to rob partygoers at a
Houston home.
   One resident opened fire, and three residents were injured in the
gunbattle, police said.
   ``Apparently, they were going to go in to rob them,'' said Sgt.
Danny James of the Houston police. He said he was not sure how many
people were at the party.
   James said one of the residents pulled a weapon and the gun
battle erupted, leaving the three dead and three residents wounded.
The injured were taken to Doctor's Hospital and listed in good
condition this morning, he said.
   Names of the three dead men and the wounded were not released.
   James said drugs may have been the motive for the robbery after a
small amount of drug paraphernalia was found in the home.
</TEXT>
