<HEAD>Justice Department Official Joining Law Firm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Assistant Attorney General Roger Marzulla, head
of the Justice Department's land and natural resources division,
resigned Monday effective Jan. 20 to join the Washington office of
an Atlanta-based law firm.
   Marzulla on Feb. 6 will join Powell, Goldstein, Frazer & Murphy
