<HEAD>Walesa Proposes Opposition Leaders for Followup TV Debate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Solidarity's Lech Walesa said Monday that
he submitted names of three prominent opposition figures to a state
television official for a proposed TV debate on union pluralism and
the economy.
   Walesa debated Alfred Miodowicz, head of Poland's official trade
unions, in a nationwide telecast on Nov. 30. At that time, he
suggested that further TV discussions take place between opposition
members and officials on various social and political problems.
