authorities now would review the list and propose a date for the TV
discussion.
   Walesa, a founder of Solidarity and 1983 Nobel Peace laureate,
said he did not believe he would take part in the debate.
   Miodowicz heads what is known as the OPZZ trade union alliance.
Walesa's group, Solidarity, is an independent trade movement that
officials crushed under martial law in 1981 and later banned.
