<DOCNO> AP881219-0271 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-19-88 1427EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-EEC-Airbus     12-19 0153</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Airbus,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC Bank to Make $133.5 Million Loan for Airbus</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUXEMBOURG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Investment Bank said Monday it
would lend 800 million French francs, or around $133.5 million, to
the French aircraft maker Aerospatiale for assembling Airbus
A330-340 jetliners.
   The bank, which is the long-term investment agency of the
European Economic Community, said the loan was for 20 years. The
interest rate wasn't disclosed.
   Aerospatiale, based in Toulouse, France, is the French member of
Airbus Industrie, a European aircraft consortium. The other members
are companies from West Germany, Britain and Spain.
   The A330-340, the largest aircraft in the Airbus range, is a
long- and medium-range plane.
   The bank said the loan is earmarked for new buildings and
installations that will be used to improve assembly and research
facilities at the site in Toulouse. Aircraft components supplied by
factories in the other Airbus member countries are assembled at the
site.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
