<HEAD>Interco To Sell Londontown Corp.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interco Inc. announced Monday it is selling its
Londontown Corp. for $178 million to a group led by senior managers
of the division.
   The sale of Londontown, which manufactures London Fog rainwear,
is part of a $2.8 billion restructuring Interco undertook to fight a
hostile takeover bid by brothers Steven and Mitchell Rales of
Washington, D.C.
   Interco has estimated its costs associated with the restructuring
will exceed $65 million. The company plans to sell off all but its
Converse Inc. and Florsheim Shoe Co. subsidiaries, its Broyhill
Furniture Industries Inc. and Lane Co. furniture companies and
possibly its Central Hardware home-improvement stores.
   The sale of Londontown would leave Interco with 10 apparel
companies, five retail stores, four footwear companies and four
furniture companies.
</TEXT>
