<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Universal-Imperial     12-19 0243</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Universal-Imperial,0253</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Universal Foods Acquiring Borden Subsidiary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Universal Foods Inc., which has been fighting a
takeover bid involving a British food conglomerate, announced Monday
it was acquiring Imperial Flavors Inc. of Winter Haven, Fla., a
Borden Inc. subsidiary.
   Milwaukee-based Universal Foods described the acquisition as
unrelated to the current $563 million takeover attempt by High
Voltage Engineering Corp., which is jointly owned by New York-based
investors Clifford Press and Laurence Levy and S&W Berisford PLC,
the British conglomerate.
   The company said the Imperial Flavors acquisition had been in the
works since early November, a month before High Voltage first
announced its offer for Universal Foods.
   High Voltage last week raised its offer for Universal to $35 a
share, a total of about $563.5 million based on Universal's roughly
16.1 million outstanding common shares. High Voltage's initial offer
of $30.50 a share was rejected by Universal earlier this month, and
the company said it would review the latest offer in due course.
   Universal's stock rose 87{ cents to $36 a share Monday on the New
York Stock Exchange.
   Universal Foods said the acquisition of Imperial Flavors, which
has annual sales of about $38 million, would ``allow for increased
sales opportunities and provide significant synergies.''
   Imperial Flavors manufactures and sells flavorings and other
ingredients to the dairy, ice cream, cultured products and bakery
industries.
   Universal Foods is a maker of food colors and flavors, yeast
products, frozen potatoes and Italian-style cheeses.
</TEXT>
